50|$|<b>Good</b> <b>agricultural</b> <b>practice</b> (GAP) are {{specific}} methods which, {{when applied to}} agriculture, create food for consumers or further processing that is safe and wholesome. While there are numerous competing definitions of what methods constitute <b>good</b> <b>agricultural</b> <b>practice</b> there are several broadly accepted schemes that producers can adhere to.|$|E
