50|$|The Food and Agricultural Organization of the United Nations (FAO) uses <b>good</b> <b>agricultural</b> <b>practice</b> as a {{collection}} of principles to apply for on-farm production and post-production processes, resulting in safe and healthy food and non-food agricultural products, while taking into account economical, social and environmental sustainability.|$|E
5000|$|Urban environments {{are known}} for their food deserts in areas of poverty, and most of the food {{available}} is shipped in. Growing Power, Inc. has a mission of [...] "helping to provide equal access to healthy, high-quality, safe and affordable food for people in all communities". Several farms in the Madison, Milwaukee, and Chicago area are <b>good</b> <b>agricultural</b> <b>practice</b> (GAP) certified.|$|E
